   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting the Escape Artists at Chimfunshi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Chimfunshi is a Chimpanzee Sanctuary based in Northern Zambia offering home to approximately 120 chimpanzees. The objective for African Impact Foundation&apos;s conservation project is to ensure the protection and rehabilitation of the chimpanzees at the sanctuary and to reduce the negative impact of humans on wildlife, in this case to to ensure that the &apos;Escape Artists&apos; have safe access to a more natural environment whilst enclosed.</narrative>
  </description>
